1. watchout the if condition's ==, make sure it's not =, vice versa
2. the right way to spell "null" is NULL
3. when in C++, don't forget using namespace std
4. keep your loop variable consistent
5. don't forget to check your if/else's span, see if it's really what you need or contain something else
6. don't mess with your loop variable, make sure it's i++ or i--
